variable.name: username
explanation: username on cluster

variable.name: composite_data_path
explanation: absolute path to directory that holds all output (and initially input) data for each experiment

variable.name: pipeline_path
explanation: absolute path to directory in home directory that contains all pipeline code (not necessarily including user-supplied code)

variable.name: temp_storage_folder
explanation: absolute path to directory in which temporary output files are placed before being compiled into results

variable.name: user_email
explanation: email of user who will receive job notifications from slurm (not relevant on unix mode)

variable.name: workload_manager
explanation: the kind of workload manager/job scheduler in the case of a HPC; or the system on which the OS is based on a computer (currently only 'slurm' for HPCs and 'unix' for computers are supported)

variable.name: max_char_num
explanation: maximum number of characters in a list of job arrays to be submitted on cluster (not relevant on unix mode)

variable.name: parallel_processors
explanation: parallel processors to use; do NOT set to >1 for processing on unix

variable.name: starting_mem
explanation: memory (in Mb) needed to run a single MLE (not relevant on unix mode)

variable.name: starting_time
explanation: time (in mins) alotted for running single MLE (not relevant on unix mode)

variable.name: max_mem
explanation: max memory (in Mb) a job is allowed to request (not relevant on unix mode)

variable.name: max_time
explanation: max time (in minutes) a job is allowed to request (not relevant on unix mode)

variable.name: max_jobs_per_batch
explanation: maximum number of jobs that can be submitted in a single batch job (if set to very high number will default to the maximum number the system allows)

variable.name: input_datafile_keys
explanation: list of variable names for input files that MLE program will look for

variable.name: input_datafile_values
explanation: list of files corresponding to each variable name listed in datafile_keys

variable.name: model
explanation: list of 'models' in which MLE fitting happens separated by vertical bars ('|')

variable.name: parameter_list
explanation: list of parameters in each model of 'model list'; parameters separated by semicolons and models are separated by vertical bars; models appear in same order as in model list

variable.name: top_level_parameters
explanation: in the case of a model whose LL is estimated hierarchically (i.e. LL_calculator only fits a subset of the parameter list while internal functions fit the rest) this is a list of parameters in each model of 'model list' that is estimated at the topmost level of the model; parameters separated by semicolons and models are separated by vertical bars; models appear in same order as in model list. If same as parameters_by_model (ie LL calculation is not hierarchical) can leave blank

variable.name: permafixed_parameters
explanation: parameters in each model that should be permanently fixed to their starting values

variable.name: starting_parameter_vals
explanation: list of starting values for each of the parameters in each model of 'model list'; parameters separated by semicolons and models are separated by vertical bars; models appear in same order as in model list and parameters in same order as in parameters by model

variable.name: min_parameter_vals
explanation: list of lower bound values for each of the parameters in each model of 'model list'; parameters separated by semicolons and models are separated by vertical bars; models appear in same order as in model list and parameters in same order as in parameters by model

variable.name: max_parameter_vals
explanation: list of upper bound values for each of the parameters in each model of 'model list'; parameters separated by semicolons and models are separated by vertical bars; models appear in same order as in model list and parameters in same order as in parameters by model

variable.name: multistart_positions
explanation: number of positions per dimension at which to start multistart (if 0 run fglobalsearch) separated by vertical bars ('|') for each model

variable.name: multistart_grid_parameters
explanation: list of parameters across which multistart selects grid points

variable.name: logspace_profile_parameters
explanation: parameters whose profiles (and MLE runs!) should be done in log rather than in linear space

variable.name: scaling_array
explanation: values that scale the approximate CI of each parameter to a consistent value (e.g. 1); for parameters estimated in logspace the scaling occurs after converting the parameter to logspace; so the distance between the natural log of the CI bounds should be scaled to the consistent value

variable.name: x_tolerance
explanation: tolerance on ML-identified values in scaled and if needed log-transformed parameter space

variable.name: fun_tolerance
explanation: tolerance on ML-identified LL or gradient

variable.name: LL_calculator
explanation: list of function/module names that calculate negative log likelihood (and possibly gradient of -LL) for every model separated by '|'

variable.name: simulator
explanation: list of function/module names that simulate data for every model separated by '|'

variable.name: nonlinear_constraint_function
explanation: list of function/module names that calculate nonlinear constraint for every model separated by '|'; if none leave blank

variable.name: pre_MLE_function
explanation: list of function/module names that perform pre-MLE-fitting functions for every model separated by '|'; if none leave blank

variable.name: post_MLE_function
explanation: list of function/module names that perform post-MLE-fitting functions for every model separated by '|'; if none leave blank

variable.name: gradient_specification
explanation: list of bools specifying whether or not LL_calculator returns a negative LL gradient for a given model

variable.name: model_code_location
explanation: absolute path to code that performs LL calculation simulation and any other necessary functions for every model; models separated by '|'

variable.name: module
explanation: language in which LL calculation etc code is written (currently available: 'matlab'; later will include support for 'python')

variable.name: profile_point_num_list
explanation: number of points to estimate fixed parameter MLE at for LL profile

variable.name: profile_lower_limits
explanation: list of min values used in the LL for each of the parameters in each model of 'model list'; parameters separated by semicolons and models are separated by vertical bars; models appear in same order as in model list and parameters in same order as in parameters by model

variable.name: profile_upper_limits
explanation: list of max values used in the LL for each of the parameters in each model of 'model list'; parameters separated by semicolons and models are separated by vertical bars; models appear in same order as in model list and parameters in same order as in parameters by model

variable.name: CI_pval
explanation: p-val of CIs identified in each model; models are separated by vertical bars; models appear in same order as in model list

variable.name: runtime_percentile
explanation: percentile of runtimes to report from within each parameter's profile point run

variable.name: sim_CI_parameters
explanation: list of parameters within each model which will get a simulation-based CI

variable.name: simulation_repeats
explanation: number times data is simulated to calculate likelihood ratio distributions for hypothesis testing in each model

variable.name: sim_mem
explanation: memory (in Mb) needed to run a single simulation (not relevant on unix mode)

variable.name: sim_time
explanation: time (in mins) alotted for running single simulation (not relevant on unix mode)

variable.name: model_comparisons
explanation: lists of sets of models to be compared; sets should be separated from each other by semicolons and models within a set should be separated from each other by colons. Parameter_names in one member of each set of models being compared must be a subset of the parameter names of the other member. Order of models in the set doesn't matter.

variable.name: response_name
explanation: name of phenotype being modeled

variable.name: fixef_category
explanation: category of fixed effects (column name in data_file)

variable.name: random_effect_names
explanation: random effects in mixed effect model

variable.name: block_effect_name
explanation: random effect by which matrix is most effectively grouped into blocks (highest random effect in hierearchy)

variable.name: intercept_parameter
explanation: parameters from parameter_list which are under fixef_name category in data and which will be treated by the mixed effect model as intercepts

variable.name: strainwise_search_type
explanation: whether search in parameter space for parameters pertaining to a single strain are done using global search with multiple starting points ('global') or a single starting point ('local')

variable.name: L
explanation: Size of x-axis (ln(mut effect)) used for initial MLE; centered on 0

variable.name: gridpower
explanation: log2(number of gridpoints for pdf determination) used for initial MLE

variable.name: strain_mean_gridpower
explanation: log2(number of gridpoints for GR diff likelihood estimation) used for initial MLE

variable.name: smoothing_kernel_sigma
explanation: sd of the kernel with which the distribution of mutational effects is convolved; recommended sd is 2^-(gridpower-2) or larger but must be 2^-(gridpower-1) or larger to work

variable.name: DFE_parameters
explanation: parameters of the DFE
